    {
      "id": "e6a85c40-f6b7-4555-8b35-76a9f745c97a",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The work draws an interesting perspective on the use of technology during the class. Authors identify behaviors in their students and make a split between preferred activities for males (information seeking and videos) and for females (social connections). Students who report multi-tasking during homework and/or class have signficantly lower GPA than their peers. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
